abstract: >-
  Continuants is a research project investigating whether long-running
  autonomous LLM agents accumulate behavioural state beyond what context
  replication captures. The work introduces the concept of agents as
  continuants (entities that persist through change), proposes a
  nine-point specification distinguishing an agent from a workflow, and
  presents two paired customer-support experiments comparing a
  memory-equipped agent against a stateless workflow control. The paper
  names and characterises the New Guy Syndrome and proposes the
  Shadow-Swap Turing Evaluations as a methodology for testing agent
  continuity across substrate change. This repository holds the
  experimental code and data; the paper is deposited on Zenodo with a
  permanent DOI (10.5281/zenodo.20349035).
